com.navis.framework.persistence.event

Interface ITxnCommitEntityEventCallback<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - object to contained the entity event data saved.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ITxnCommitEntityEventVOCallback
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventBusCommitEventCallback

    public interface ITxnCommitEntityEventCallback<V>
    This interface represents a transaction POST COMMIT callback associated with a ITxnCommitEntityEventInterceptor, where the entity event data saved is processed.
    Author:
    Gisella Saavedra, Mar 14, 2012
    See Also:
    ITxnCommitEntityEventInterceptor

      Processes a notification of entity updates already committed within a transaction.

    • Method Detail

      • process

        int process(@NotNull
            java.lang.String inEventId,
            long inEventSequence,
            @NotNull
            EntityId inEntityId,
            int inUpdateType,
            @NotNull
            V inUpdateDetails)
        Processes a notification of entity updates already committed within a transaction. A non-negative return value indicates the number of updates processed, while a negative return value indicates an error situation due to which none of the updates were processed. Implementations should log an appropriate message for any situation due to which an entity update reflected in the inEntityValueHolder was not processed successfully.
        Parameters:
        inEventId - identifier related to the event, intended to be useful for accounting / tracking
        inEventSequence - sequence of the event, related to its identifier
        inEntityId - identifier of the updated entity
        inUpdateType - type of update that was made to the entity
        inUpdateDetails - details about the updates that were made
        Returns:
        the number of entities actually processed (>= 0), or a negative error code, such as -1 if the inUpdateType was not recognized
